		<p class="text-center bottom-buffer"><%= link_to "Back to Intro", principles_intro_path %> | <%= link_to "Skip to Advanced", principles_advanced_path %></p>
		<p><ol class="big-text">
			<li>When applying BBQ sauce during the BBQ process.  Wait until the meal is almost cooked and apply the sauce on the last few sides.  If you apply too liberally or too early in the cooking process it will burn and form a less-than-tasty coating for your creation.</li>
			<li>Rub your grill surface with a paper towel or brush with olive oil before you grill.  This will prevent veggies, burgers, chicken, or fish from sticking.</li>
			<li>Never wash beef or pork prior to grilling, but do rinse chicken or fish in water before grilling to lessen bacteria.</li>
			<li>Pat down meat with paper towels before applying a marinade or other pre grill seasoning.</li>
			<li>Use sea salt and olive oil as a marinade for steak.  Apply liberally to both sides and let sit.  The combination will caramelize and seal in juices of the meat when seared.</li>
		</ol></p>
